  "rationale": "<p>The correct answer is 2. The slope-intercept form of an equation for a line is <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"y equals, m x plus b\"></span>, where <span class=\"italic\">m</span> is the slope and <span class=\"italic\">b</span> is the <span class=\"italic\">y</span>-coordinate of the <span class=\"italic\">y</span>-intercept. Two ordered pairs, <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x sub 1 comma y sub 1 \"></span> and <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x sub 2 comma y sub 2\"></span>, can be used to compute the slope using the formula <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"m equals, the fraction with numerator y sub 2, minus y sub 1, and denominator x sub 2, minus x sub 1, end fraction\"></span>. It&rsquo;s given that <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"f of 0 equals 18 \"></span> and <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"f of 1 equals 20 \"></span>; therefore, the two ordered pairs for this line are <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"0 comma 18 \"></span> and <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"1 comma 20\"></span>. Substituting these values for <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x sub 1 comma y sub 1\"></span> and <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x sub 2 comma y sub 2 \"></span> gives <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"the fraction with numerator 20 minus 18, and denominator 1 minus 0, end fraction, equals, the fraction 2 over 1\"></span>, or 2.</p>\n",
